Let me re-analyze the mutation more carefully.

The mutation changes `if(!Array.isArray(array))` to `if(true)`.

When `if(true)` runs on an actual array:
- `Object.keys(array)` returns string indices like `"0"`, `"1"`, `"2"` 
- Then maps `k => array[k]` which returns the values

So for `[1, 2, 3]`, both paths return `[1, 2, 3]`. The extra property trick didn't work because `Object.keys` on arrays with extra properties... let me verify: `Object.keys([1,2,3])` with `arr.extra = 99` would return `["0", "1", "2", "extra"]`, so the mutated code WOULD include `99`.

Wait - the previous test should have worked. Let me reconsider why it passed on mutated code too.

Actually, maybe the issue is that `arr['extra'] = 99` - `Object.keys` on an array only returns numeric indices by default. Let me verify: actually `Object.keys` DOES include non-index string properties on arrays.

Let me think differently - what if I pass an object (not an array)? With original: converts via `Object.keys`. With mutated: also converts via `Object.keys`. Same behavior.

What about passing an actual array where the conversion changes something? The conversion does `Object.keys(array).map(k => array[k])` - for a normal array this is identical. 

The real difference: with `if(true)`, the `i` counter iterates over the NEW array (result of map), not the original. But values are the same...

Unless I use a sparse array! `[1,,3]` - `Object.keys` returns `["0", "2"]`, skipping the hole.

```typescript
import values from "../../../../../../../../../../../subject_repositories/pull-stream/sources/values.js";

describe("values source", () => {
  it("should preserve sparse array holes when input is an array", (done) => {
    const arr = [1, , 3] as any[];  // sparse array
    const source = values(arr);
    const results: any[] = [];
    function read() {
      source(null, (end: any, val: any) => {
        if (end === true) {
          expect(results).toHaveLength(3); // original preserves length=3, mutated gets length=2
          done();
        } else if (end) { done(end); } else { results.push(val); read(); }
      });
    }
    read();
  });
});
```

